{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17489613","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17489613"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T04:23:01+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T04:23:01+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"701"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"701","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/701"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.12,0.02,0.76,0.07,0.02]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"701"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"110281"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"701","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/701"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"701"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"92552"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"2"},{"type":"tags","id":"24"},{"type":"tags","id":"64"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"1036"},{"type":"tags","id":"1114"},{"type":"tags","id":"2765"},{"type":"tags","id":"4953"},{"type":"tags","id":"4961"},{"type":"tags","id":"4987"},{"type":"tags","id":"4992"},{"type":"tags","id":"7861"},{"type":"tags","id":"10962"},{"type":"tags","id":"11625"},{"type":"tags","id":"11630"},{"type":"tags","id":"11642"},{"type":"tags","id":"11650"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"8444"},{"type":"contributions","id":"8805"},{"type":"contributions","id":"41307"},{"type":"contributions","id":"42130"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"110281","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/110281"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 69-year-old man presents to a large metropolitan emergency department with acute onset, left-sided chest pain, crushing in nature and radiating to the left jaw. He is alert, with a blood pressure of 130/90 mmHg and has an oxygen saturation of 98% breathing room air.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most appropriate next step?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Intravenous glyceryl trinitrate infusion","Administer high-flow oxygen by Hudson mask","Perform an ECG","Subcutaneous morphine","Perform bedside point-of-care troponin"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":[],"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EIn this patient the immediate concern is for an acute coronary syndrome (ACS), especially a STEMI (ST-elevation myocardial infarction). While there are atypical presentations, the patient in the stem presents typically with crushing chest pain that radiates to the left arm or jaw.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EWhilst a number of investigations and treatments will be done promptly in this patient, the priority must be to\u003Cstrong\u003E perform an ECG \u003C/strong\u003Ewithin ten minutes of the first acute clinical contact. This is important to facilitate diagnosis, risk stratification and further management such activating a code STEMI in a hospital with an acute percutaneous coronary intervention service.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EAdministering \u003Cstrong\u003Ehigh-flow oxygen by Hudson mask \u003C/strong\u003Eis not indicated in this patient as his oxygen saturations are 98%. Studies have shown that oxygen therapy have no cardiovascular effect in normoxic patients.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EOpioid medication such as \u003Cstrong\u003Emorphine\u003C/strong\u003E may be used initially to help control pain. Further management, if required, may be given as an \u003Cstrong\u003Eintravenous glyceryl trinitrate infusion\u003C/strong\u003E.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPoint of care troponin\u003C/strong\u003E would be able to provide a rapid troponin level when access to hospital care and/or laboratory services is limited. Serial troponins should be done on all patients, but an ECG remains the priority.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["An ECG should be performed within 10 minutes in any patient presenting with suspected ACS.","Oxygen therapy is not indicated in normoxic patients with STEMI diagnosed."],"references":["Chew DP, Scott IA, Cullen L, et al. National Heart Foundation of Australia and Cardiac Society of Australia and New Zealand: Australian clinical guidelines for the management of acute coronary syndromes 2016. The Medical journal of Australia. 205(3):128-33. 2016","de Alencar Neto JN. Morphine, Oxygen, Nitrates, and Mortality Reducing Pharmacological Treatment for Acute Coronary Syndrome: An Evidence-based Review. Cureus. 2018 Jan 25;10(1):e2114. doi: 10.7759/cureus.2114. PMID: 29581926; PMCID: PMC5866121.","Nickson C. Life in the fast lane. STEMI Management. 2020 Dec. https://litfl.com/stemi-management/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"92552"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"701"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"92552","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/92552"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-07-29T13:52:47+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-07-29T13:54:04+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"701"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"110281"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"2","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/2"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\udec0","name":"Cardiology","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:47:21+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"24","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/